I think this is my body. Whenever I wear a turtle neck or something that is close to my neck, my neck looks shorter than it actually is. And it's so true with the flouncy blouses. My mom once bought me a flouncy blouse and my shoulders look larger than my actual shoulders  And I always need a waist definition, either a tight-fit top or high-waist pants. So I would love to see how to dress in this body type  But is it possible to have this body type when I'm short-legged? If so, then I guess this truly is my body type.
